# Find the service which makes it possible to run specific tasks following a regular
# schedule

'cron' is the name of the service.
You can use the command 'crontab' for running it. 
'crontab -e' for getting into the file where you can scheduale commands.
(use the homepage https://crontab.guru to get help how to scheduale)
'crontab -l' will list your commands after you have added them.
